-- Magnitude 5.8 earthquake strikes southwest Mexico -USGS
-- By John Stonestreet
-- Wed Aug 13, 2014 03:21AM EDT
-- None



Aug 13 (Reuters) - A magnitude 5.8 earthquake struck the southwest Mexican state of Oaxaca on Tuesday, the U.S. Geological Survey said.

The quake had a depth of 10 km and its epicentre was 16 km (10 miles) west of the town of Pinotepa Nacional.